BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"PEN America": "https://www.eventbrite.com/e/dr-ibram-x-kendi-friends-chain-of-ideas-a-global-conversation-tickets-1984646817055"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Pen America": "https://pen.org/event/chain-of-ideas/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:pen_america
SUMMARY:Dr. Ibram X. Kendi &amp\; Friends: Chain of Ideas\, a Global Conve
 rsation
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T143000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260321T143000
UID:b6d666493e97de6681d6d09c0116ae9c@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:To honor the International Day for the Elimination of Racial D
 iscrimination\, please join PEN America for a free virtual conversation wi
 th the National Book Award-winning historian of\nStamped from the Beginnin
 g\n\, Dr. Ibram X. Kendi\, and leaders from human rights organizations fro
 m across the globe. Dr. Kendi’s newest book\,\nChain of Ideas: The Origi
 ns of Our Authoritarian Age\n\, charts how “great replacement theory” 
 (GRT) has moved from the margins to become the most dominant political the
 ory of our time—and what we can do to safeguard democracy from this insi
 dious threat.\nIn our fast-shifting political landscape\, most people are 
 unfamiliar with this theory’s origins and its spread\, which isn’t a c
 oincidence. In\nChain of Ideas\n\, Ibram X. Kendi uses exacting and clear 
 prose to uncover the roots of great replacement theory and its various mut
 ations around the world. It is an unsettling but indispensable global hist
 ory of how great replacement theory brought humanity into this authoritari
 an age—and how we can free ourselves from it.\nThe event will start with
  a conversation between\nDr. Kendi\nand\nRaqib Naik\n\, Executive Director
  of\nThe Center for the Study of Organized Hate\n\, examining the roots of
  GRT and the threats it presents.\nThen in conversation\nAshwini K.P.\n\, 
 the\nUN’s 6th Special Rapporteur on contemporary forms of racism\n\,\nNo
 ah Bullock\,\nExecutive Director of\nCristosal\n&\nDr. Kendi\nwill discuss
  where they are seeing GRT show up today and in what forms.\nFinally\,\nDr
 . Kendi\n\,\nRethabile Ratsomo\nfrom the\nAhmed Kathrada Foundation\n\, an
 d\nZélie Heran\n\, the Head of the Legal Department at\nSOS Racisme\n\, w
 ill share the initiatives and approaches being taken to combat GRT.\nFeatu
 ring leaders from  the Center for the Study of Organized Hate\, the UN’
 s 6th Special Rapporteur on contemporary forms of racism\, Cristosal\, the
  Ahmed Kathrada Foundation\, and SOS Racisme\, this event will introduce a
 ttendees to the dangers of GRT and provide a path forward.\nAbout\nChain o
 f Ideas\n:\nRecall the w
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://pen.org/event/chain-of-ideas/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
