SUMMARY:The Law of Discrimination in the Journalism Workplace (Webinar)
DESCRIPTION:Media Law for Journalists: The Law of Discrimination in the Journalism Workplace  \nDate/Time: Tuesday\, April 21 at 6pm ET \nSummary: This workshop will assist you in understanding the fundamentals of employment discrimination law applicable to news organizations and journalistic endeavors\, including differences between employees and contractors; discrimination in the context of hiring\, discipline\, and termination; different forms that discrimination takes; and responses to incidents of discrimination. The session also explores harassment\, a close legal cousin of discrimination.   \nSpeaker(s):   \n\nAnaeli Petisco-Rojas\, Vice President\, Employment Law\, TelevisaUnivision\nJamila Brinson\, Partner\,Labor and Employment\, Jackson Walker LLP \n\nRegister here: https://nahj.memberclicks.net/MediaLawdiscrimination
URL:https://nahj.org/event/the-law-of-discrimination-in-the-journalism-workplace-webinar/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nahj.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Media-Law-Training-8.png
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-ID:tiny_news_members_only
X-SOURCE:Tiny News Members Only
DTSTART:20260421T200000Z
DTEND:20260421T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260319T022535Z
UID:6ubpt0oc287io5a9jsp01q02vl@google.com
CREATED:20260220T203220Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>From Founder to Leader: What to Consider as Your Org
 anization Evolves</strong></p><p>As your organization grows\, your role has
  to grow with it. What made you a strong founder is not always what will ma
 ke you an effective leader at the next stage.</p><p>This interactive sessio
 n invites you to pause and reflect on that transition.</p><p>We’ll begin by
  grounding ourselves in what leadership means to each of us\, then explore 
 the distinction between “founder mode” and “leader mode.” From there\, we’l
 l work through a set of practical\, self-reflective questions designed to h
 elp you assess where you are and what may need to shift.</p><p>We’ll examin
 e four key areas:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Identity and attachment:</strong> W
 hat is the line between you and the organization?Who are you without the da
 ily hustle of building? Where might ego\, control or fear be shaping decisi
 ons?</p></li><li><p><strong>Strategic clarity:</strong> Are you leading fro
 m a clear north star\, or reacting to urgent demands?</p></li><li><p><stron
 g>Hard conversations:</strong> What are you avoiding that a leader must add
 ress?</p></li><li><p><strong>Sustainable leadership:</strong> Are you build
 ing a role that can last\, or one that depends entirely on your personal ov
 erextension?</p></li></ul><p>You’ll also be guided through a <strong>person
 al SWOT analysis</strong> tailored to your leadership evolution\, with a li
 ve example to help you think concretely about strengths\, blind spots\, ris
 ks and opportunities.</p><p>We’ll close with Q&amp\;A and an invitation: ch
 oose one leadership question to sit with this week and complete your own pe
 rsonal SWOT. Those who sign up for a follow-up coaching session can bring t
 heir reflection for deeper discussion and accountability.</p><p>This sessio
 n is designed for founders who sense that the next stage requires something
  different from them and are ready to lead more intentionally\, not just wo
 rk harder.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260220T204650Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:From Founder to Leader: What to Consider as Your Organization Evolv
 es
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sabew": "https://sabew.org/event/crafting-a-resume-that-increases-your-odds-of-landing-in-the-yes-pile/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:sabew
X-SOURCE:Sabew
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260422T140000
DTSTAMP:20260318T222534
CREATED:20260318T152735Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260318T153158Z
UID:70136-1776862800-1776866400@sabew.org
SUMMARY:Crafting a resume that increases your odds of landing in the ‘yes’ pile
DESCRIPTION:If you’re looking to make a career move\, the first hurdle you’ll likely face is getting your resume past the applicant tracking system. This webinar will offer tips on how to format your resume to boost the likelihood it will be seen by a human and get the consideration it deserves. The panel will discuss how to select keywords to use so that once your application makes it through any filters\, it will impress the hiring manager. You will receive actionable advice\, such as which tools to use to test your resume and how to get AI to work for you in your job search. \nIf you lost your job in 2026\, SABEW wants to help. We are offering one-year complimentary memberships for those who have been affected by newsroom cuts. Join SABEW\, the association for business journalists\, to access virtual training sessions\, like this one\, and other membership benefits. Complete this form and someone from SABEW will be in contact with you. \nPanelists:\nSarah Babbage\, news team lead at Bloomberg\nHilke Schellman\, professor in New York University’s Arthur L. Carter Journalism Institute\, author of “The Algorithm: How AI Decides who Gets Hired\, Monitored\, Promoted and Fired\, and Why We Need to Fight Back Now” \nRegistration:\nThis is a free webinar\, but you must register below to receive the Zoom link.
URL:https://sabew.org/event/crafting-a-resume-that-increases-your-odds-of-landing-in-the-yes-pile/
CATEGORIES:Virtual Training
END:VEVENT
