BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sabew": "https://sabew.org/event/sabew26/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:sabew
X-SOURCE:Sabew
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260507
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260510
DTSTAMP:20260318T222534
CREATED:20250730T220320Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260313T162658Z
UID:66733-1778112000-1778371199@sabew.org
SUMMARY:#SABEW26 Annual Conference
DESCRIPTION:Conference FAQ’s\n*View the tentative sessions at this year’s conference*\nMark your calendars! SABEW\, the Society for Advancing Business Editing and Writing\, will hold its annual conference\, Thursday\, May 7 – Saturday\, May 9\, 2026\, at the DoubleTree by Hilton Philadelphia Center City. \nWhether you are a newsroom leader\, early/mid-career journalist\, academic\, student\, or PR pro\, SABEW’s annual conference is tailor made for you\, with diverse programming that will allow you to take home new ideas to use in your stories\, newsrooms\, or classrooms. Don’t miss the opportunity to network with other colleagues\, hear from top industry leaders\, and celebrate the winners of the Best in Business awards. \nThis year’s event will also feature a stop on RTDNA’s World Tour\, bringing its signature focus on broadcast and modern newsroom leadership. Through interactive discussions and practical takeaways\, Radio Television Digital News Association trainers offer insights into audience-centered coverage\, ethical leadership and newsroom culture. The World Tour stop is made possible through a partnership between RTDNA and the SABEW\, supported by the National Endowment for Financial Education (NEFE) — reflecting a shared commitment to elevating journalism training and expanding access to professional development across newsrooms. \nThe conference will also include career enhancing collaborations with AAJA-NY\, American City Business Journals\, Bright Data\, ESPN\, IRE\, The Commonwealth Fund\, The National Institute for Health Care Management Foundation\, RTDNA\, and The Wharton School\, The University of Pennsylvania. \nRegister today and we look forward to seeing you in Philadelphia! \nRegistration \nEarly-bird registration is $300 for SABEW members\, $375 for nonmembers\, and $75 for students. Early bird pricing ends Wednesday\, April 1. Beginning Thursday\, April 2\, the price for SABEW members will increase to $350 and $425 for nonmembers. The student price will remain the same. Purchase your ticket below. \nBest in Business Awardees can register at a discounted rate. Please email awards@sabew.org to request the discount code. \nCancellations \nCancellations must be sent via email to logistics@sabew.org. All cancellations must be in writing. There is a $50 processing fee for all cancellations until April 9. After that date\, requests for refunds will be considered on a case-by-case basis. \nHotel Information \nDoubleTree Philadelphia Center City\n237 S Broad St\nPhiladelphia\, PA 19107 \nThe room rate is $209 per night\, plus tax for single/double rooms (currently 15.5% + 0.75%) *subject to change. Rooms are available in the discounted block until Monday\, April 13\, 2026\, or until the block is full (whichever comes first.) If you need to cancel your reservation\, you must do so 72 hours prior to arrival to avoid any cancellation fees. \nTo make a reservation\, click here. \nFellowship Opportunities \nFellowship opportunities are available for female journalists\, journalists of color\, and business journalists who represent underserved areas to attend the #SABEW26 conference. For more information and to apply\, please click here. Applications are due by Tuesday\, March 31. \nSpeed mentoring \nSit down for a one-on-one conversation with a newsroom editor or hiring manager during this hands-on session at the #SABEW26 conference. Mentees will have the chance to have their resume or clips reviewed\, practice their story pitch and brush up on their interviewing skills. It’s a great opportunity to make new connections\, seek career advice or ask questions about breaking into the industry. \nTo participate as a mentor or mentee\, complete this form by 5 p.m. ET\, Monday\, April 27. All participants must be registered for the conference. The session is open to early-career journalists and students. Space is limited. \nSponsors and Exhibitors \nExhibitor and sponsor opportunities are available. Lock in your space early for the best prices and to ensure a spot. Contact Stephanie Klimstra at sklimstra@sabew.org for additional details. \nShop SABEW \nGear up with SABEW t-shirts\, sweatshirts\, and more! Visit the SABEW store today. \n  \nThank you to our sponsors and exhibitors!\n  \n \n 
URL:https://sabew.org/event/sabew26/
CATEGORIES:Conference,In-Person Training,Networking
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://sabew.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/26_ConferenceLogo_H_1500x500.jpg
END:VEVENT
